---
Midgaard's relationship to the corridor is primarily extractive and archival: expeditions catalog inscriptions, salvage crews recover artifacts, and archival institutions maintain provenance chains giving artifacts commercial legitimacy.
The Magistrate Ledgerhouse holds the most comprehensive western archive: inscription rubbings from all three pyramid sites, Cairn Broker caravan manifests, and Southern Oasis Mortuary Circle casualty ledgers.
Midgaard recognizes Water Court documents from all three oases in city tribunals; artifacts enter through standard customs only with oasis authentication.
The Reckoning Faction has sought access to sealed archive materials at multiple corridor sites for three generations: Nightfall catacombs records, Sultan's Palace harmonization ledgers, and the Khepra-Lesh sealed reliquary index.
The academic position on the Black Sun Shard connection: archival evidence for the corridor's anti-amnesia function is acknowledged but cosmic cause is treated as unresolved.
Midgaard scholars use Kowloon's functional Keeper-of-Measure legal methodology as a living reference for understanding corridor inscription syntax.

flags KOWLOON
---
Kowloon preserves the most functionally intact Keeper-of-Measure legal methodology through its Jade Magistracy and Neon Covenant, maintaining living practice of the volumetric-legal layer the corridor built civilization on.
House Jien imported Keeper-era legal formatting via refugees fleeing the Solar Court's administrative collapse; Kowloon's bureaucratic apparatus is a distant descendant of the desert's charter-road administration.
Kowloon's one-ledger, one-ration-code principle descends from the same calibration discipline that produced the oasis intake sluice systems.
Disaster risk assessment for corridor stability is calibrated against Northern Oasis flow reports as an early warning indicator.
The Ash Cult frames the corridor's collapse as divine punishment for scholars who tried to govern what should not be governed — a reading the Jade Magistracy dismisses as fabrication.
Kowloon's maritime insurance rates for eastern corridor cargo are linked to Northern Oasis flow report assessments; corridor instability affects coastal port throughput measurably.

